HEADWORD: Unmerciful
<hw>Un*mer"ci*ful</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Not merciful;
indisposed to mercy or grace; cruel; inhuman; merciless; unkind.</def>
-- <wordforms><wf>Un*mer"ci*ful*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Un*mer"ci*ful*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unmerciless</ent>⟦br⟧
